description:
In my interview with Joe for Jazz Master Summit, http://www.jazzmastersumm.com I asked him if he believed there was an element of courage that went with playing in your own unique musical voice. Is there an element of bravery that goes with playing in a way that isn't like the standard way others approach your instrument?

He told a very cool story about Joe Henderson's reaction to a solo Joe (Lovano) played and you'll like how he answers the question.
fulltitle: Joe Lovano on the courage to play with your unique musical voice
